						<div class="postbody">Do any notable Master System games use sprite scaling? The obvious solution for SMS flipping (a bit reverse lookup table) could do scaling (a bit deletion lookup table) with very little overhead, as seen <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=12055" class="postlink">here</a> where I scale a 32x48 sprite at 15 fps on an NES.</div>

